answerText: benzene [prompt on C6H6][10] This molecule is the major product of a Birch reduction on benzene. Meanwhile, the minor product has double bonds at the one and three positions on the ring.

question: Question: Name some things about six-membered cyclic molecules, [10] This six-membered annulene contains a system of three conjugated bonds. Methylating this compound yields toluene.
